Reasoning: The paper discusses a computational model of how ideas evolve in a society of interacting individuals, which involves exploring the impact of biological, cognitive, and social phenomena on the fitness and diversity of cultural transmissible actions. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) due to the use of a computational model, Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) due to the focus on social phenomena, Software Engineering (cs.SE) due to the development of a software model, Machine Learning (cs.LG) due to the exploration of cognitive phenomena, and Cybernetics (cs.CY) due to the study of the interaction between biological and computational systems.
